# CSS Conflict Prevention and Specificity Management

## 🚨 **CSS Specificity Rules**

- **Use theme classes** when possible for maximum stability
- **Avoid deep nesting** (max 3 levels)
- **Prefer class selectors** over element selectors
- **Use attribute selectors** sparingly and only for stable attributes

## 📋 **Namespace Strategy**

```css
/* GOOD: Use theme classes when available */
.theme-layout-navbar .navbar__item {
  /* Custom navbar styling */
}

/* AVOID: Deep nesting with implementation details */
.navbar .navbar__inner .navbar__items .navbar__item {
  /* Fragile styling */
}
```

## 🔢 **Z-Index Management**

```css
/* Define z-index scale in CSS variables */
:root {
  --z-navbar: 1000;
  --z-sidebar: 999;
  --z-backdrop: 998;
  --z-content: 1;
}

/* Use variables consistently */
.navbar {
  z-index: var(--z-navbar);
}
```

## 📍 **Positioning Conflicts**

- **Fixed positioning** should use `z-index` management
- **Sticky positioning** should respect parent containers
- **Absolute positioning** should have defined boundaries

